{{/* acid_badge — click-to-copy ACID anchor (web-ui.SHARED.1, web-ui.LOCAL.4).

The dot argument is the literal ACID string (e.g.
"sync.GIT.3" or "spec-format.RECIPE.6.2"). The badge sets data-acid
to the same value so the clipboard handler in static/clipboard.js
picks it up regardless of whitespace handling.

Variant control: pass an "Sm" key in a map for the smaller pill
shape used inside dense tables / requirement bodies. The shared
struct shape is documented as web.AcidBadge in handlers; templates
remain field-tolerant for callers that pass a raw string. */}}

{{define "acid_badge"}}
{{- if eq (printf "%T" .) "string" -}}
<a class="acid" data-acid="{{.}}" href="#" title="copy acid">{{.}}</a>
{{- else -}}
<a class="acid{{if .Small}} acid-sm{{end}}{{if .Class}} {{.Class}}{{end}}"
   data-acid="{{.ACID}}"
   href="{{if .Href}}{{.Href}}{{else}}#{{end}}"
   title="copy acid">{{.ACID}}</a>
{{- end -}}
{{end}}
